L["encounter:61408"] = "Spread out so that only 1 person gets hit with Inferno Charge." -- Adarogg in Ragefire Chasm
L["encounter:61412"] = "No special mechanics, Tank and Spank, don't stand in puddles" -- Dark Shaman Koranthal in Ragefire Chasm
L["encounter:61463"] = "Watch for lava spit, boss submerges every 5 spits" -- Slagmaw in Ragefire Chasm
L["encounter:61528"] = "Ranged spread out to avoid slam, watch for enrage at 30%" -- Lava Guard Gordoth in Ragefire Chasm
L["encounter:47162"] = "Tank and Spank on 1st Phase, expect damage spikes to tank when he does Fists of Flame/Frost\n\nPhase 2 he shoots frost bombs on the blue patches on the ground, don't stand in these. (CHECK HEROIC DATA FOR L85 INSTANCE)|cff1eff00Heroic|r\n\nPhase 1 same as normal, in Phase 2 the frost bombs spawn adds and he also casts a CLOCKWISE rotating firewall avoid it at all cost. Walk round the boss with this but don't touch it, all the time killing adds the boss and avoiding frost" -- Glubtok in Deadmines
L["encounter:47296"] = "The Lumbering Oaf will engage you, Tank and Spank him whilst avoiding the bombs on the floor. Occasionally people will get a Bomb on their chest or they will be picked up and charged. BIG HEALING on them then\n\nOnce he's dead just keep chasing the small guy and dpsing him down while he plants bombs on people.|cff1eff00Heroic|r\n\nNo real changes for Heroic" -- Helix Gearbreaker in Deadmines
L["encounter:43778"] = "Put a MDPS in the robot... he stands at the bottom picking up the adds. Spam 1-1-2 until they are dead. Don't let any through\n\nHeals and ranged sit mid-ramp and the tank takes the boss to the top of the ramp. During Whirlwind EVERYONE gets out of the way, during charge the targetted person needs to run down the slope|cff1eff00Heroic|r\n\nNo real changes for Heroic" -- Foe Reaper 5000 in Deadmines
L["encounter:47626"] = "(Heroic Tactics only) High DPS required. Tank him with your back to the wall and everyone else close by so the tank can grab the adds when they spawn. You could also try in the captain's cabin\n\nat 75% and 50% he vanishes and adds spawn, burn them asap, the boss will come back soon and adds keep spawning, try to burn the adds quickly whilst still dpsing the boss. Blow all your cooldowns at 25% when he and the adds go nuts|cff1eff00Heroic|r\n\nNo real changes for Heroic" -- Admiral Ripsnarl in Deadmines
L["encounter:47739"] = "Ranged attack the boss, healer... heal, Melee and Tank run round eating 1 bad then 1 good food.|cff1eff00Heroic|r\n\nNo real changes for Heroic" -- Captain Cookie in Deadmines
L["encounter:3671"] = "Heals herself and can sleep a party member" -- Lady Anacondra in Wailing Caverns
L["encounter:3669"] = "Comes with 2 snake adds and can heal himself. Kill the adds first" -- Lord Cobrahn in Wailing Caverns
L["encounter:3670"] = "Has a heal and a sleep" -- Lord Pythas in Wailing Caverns
L["encounter:3673"] = "Has a heal and a sleep" -- Lord Serpentis in Wailing Caverns
L["encounter:5775"] = "Hits Very very hard. also has a knockdown/root AoE ability." -- Verdan the Everliving in Wailing Caverns
L["encounter:3653"] = "Tank & Spank" -- Kresh in Wailing Caverns
L["encounter:5912"] = "Tank & Spank" -- Deviate Faerie Dragon (Rare) in Wailing Caverns
L["encounter:3674"] = "Tank & Spank, watch for chain lightning" -- Skum in Wailing Caverns
L["encounter:3654"] = "15s Sleep, a fear and an AoE Stun... waves of adds spawn and then the boss will appear after the 2nd wave is dead" -- Mutanus the Devourer in Wailing Caverns
L["encounter:46962"] = "Everyone try to Interrupt/Dispel Pain and Suffering. Healer don't keep people at full, but just enough to survive wracking pains (heroic only). After Asphyxiate everyone should use a Healthstone/Pot/lightwell/whatever.\n\nIf you can Vanish/Feign/AMS/Iceblock try and do that when he starts asphyxiate. Afterwards interrupt his stay of execution (which heals him AND you).\n\nAt 25% he will cast a partwide DoT. Bloodlust/cooldown/do anything to burn this asap. Healers try to save mana for this stage. (heroic only)" -- Baron Ashbury in Shadowfang Keep
L["encounter:46963"] = "Red light/Green light. Fairly easy boss... his poison and ice attacks are easy to handle, just be careful when he casts unstable mixture.\n\nIf he casts RED, then STOP MOVING. If he casts GREEN, then KEEP MOVING. Not following this will mean you take a lot of damage." -- Lord Walden in Shadowfang Keep
L["encounter:46964"] = "If you don't have a decurser, then good luck healing. Fight starts with some adds that can be easily AoEd/burnt while tank faces the boss away from party\n\nHe will then do pistol barrage which is a Conal damage effect followed by cursed bullets - a damage spike AND DoT. Decurse/interrupt this if you can. 10 seconds later more cursed bullets, then the adds will come again." -- Lord Godfrey in Shadowfang Keep
L["encounter:3887"] = "T&S with adds. Burn the adds down when they spawn.|cff1eff00Heroic|r\n\nCursed Veil does shadow damage and reduces healing by 75%" -- Baron Silverlaine in Shadowfang Keep
L["encounter:4278"] = "Tank away from the party and don't stand in the void zones. 2 Adds will spawn, DPS them down (shackle if possible) the Wailing guards do an AoE Spell lock so don't get close" -- Commander Springvale in Shadowfang Keep
L["encounter:46383"] = "Tank & Spank, He uses Wildly Stabbing witch should be avoided if possible and Sweep which will hit the tank + 1 nearby player, Vanishes around 60 and 40 % Health and will appear behind a random Player, tank should get aggro soon as possible" -- Randolph Moloch in Stormwind Stockade
L["encounter:46264"] = "Tank & Spank, Party should avoid his Rain of Fire a 5 yard AOE, and Healer needs to make sure players hit by overheat survive the DoT damage" -- Lord Overheat in Stormwind Stockade
L["encounter:46254"] = "Tank & Spank, He will use Maddening Call as a group wide AOE damage and slight slowing Debuff, and will Enrage for more Damage and Attack speed at 30% Health" -- Hogger in Stormwind Stockade
