L["encounter:72057"] ="++ORDOS\n\nMagma Crush: Stay within 20 yards of Boss to split damage.\n\nBurning Soul: Move 8 yards away from others to avoid damaging them.\n\nPool of Fire: Move away from pools.\n\nAncient Flame: Move away from orbs."

--SIEGE OF ORGRIMMAR
-- Immerseus 
L["encounter:71543"] = "++IMMERSEUS\n\nINTRO\n\nBoss starts with full Corruption bar. Bring to 0 by killing and healing Adds.\n\n+BOSS PHASE\n\nALL\n\nStay spread.\nSha Bolt: Move from black pools.\nSwirl: Avoid moving blue discs and Boss's water jet.\nSeeping Sha: Stay out of center.\n\nDPS\n\nAttack Boss.\n\nHEALERS\n\nSha Bolt: Heal raid-wide damage.\n\nTANKS\n\nFace Boss away from raid.\nCorrosive Blast: Swap on debuff drop.\n\n+ADD PHASE\n\nDPS\n\nSlow and kill hostile Adds. At death, damage buff if within 10 yards.\n\nHEALERS\n\nSlow and heal friendly Adds. At full heal, mana buff if within 12 yards.\nHeal raid-wide damage when Adds reach Boss." 
-- The Fallen Protectors 
L["encounter:71475"] = "++FALLEN PROTECTORS\n\nINTRO\n\nThree Boses. \nSwitch every 33% to trigger phase changes. \nKill all three within 10 seconds of each other.\n\n+MAIN PHASES\n\nALL\n\nStay spread.\n\nDPS\n\nUse cleaves on Rook and Sun.\nSwitch assigned target every 33%.\nOrder: Rook, He, Sun. Repeat.\nKill Adds.\n\nHEALERS\n\nBane: Dispel.\nGarrote: Heal target.\nCalamity: Heal target.\nVengeful Strikes: Heal Tank.\n\nTANKS\n\nOne on Rook and Sun.\nOther on He.\nFace Rook away from raid.\nVengeful Strikes: Strafe.\nMove He away from raid.\nHe's Noxious Poison: Move from pool.\nHe's Instant Poison: Use cooldown.\nHe's Gouge: Face away from Boss.\n\n+DESPERATE MEASURES PHASES\n\nROOK PHASE\nTank Misery away from raid.\nMisery's Defiled Ground: Move.\nGloom's Corruption Shock: Interrupt.\nSorrow's Inferno Strike: STACK briefly on target.\nAdd kill order: Sorrow, Gloom, Misery.\n\nHE PHASE\nPass Mark of Anguish to He Tank.\nKill Anguish.\n\nSUN PHASE\nAdds do not need tanking.\nStack in Meditative Field.\nMelee kill Adds inside.\nRanged kill Adds outside." 
-- Norushen 
L["encounter:71965"] = "++NORUSHEN\n\nINTRO\n\nPlayers have Corruption bar starting with 75 Corruption. \nCorruption weakens damage, healing, or defense. \nCan enter Test Realm to Purify, reducing Corruption.\n\n+NORMAL REALM\n\nALL\n\nBlind Hatred: Move from beam.\nSmall Adds: Block projectiles going to Boss.\n\nDPS\n\nPriorities: Manifestations (Large) > Essences (Small) > Boss.\nHero and damage cooldowns at 50%.\n\nHEALERS\n\nUnleashed Anger: Heal Tank.\nBurst of Anger: Raid-wide heals.\n\nTANKS\n\nTank Boss.  \nPickup Manifestations. \nSelf Doubt: Swap on return from Test Realm.\nResidual Corruption Globes: Soak.\n\n+TEST REALMS\n\nClick globe to enter.\nTanks: Priority. Alternate entry.\nDPS: Sequence entry. Once each.\n\nDPS\n\nKill Adds.\nManifestation: Strafe from frontal cone.\nEssences: Avoid line of fire. Attack from back when shielded.\n\nHEALERS\n\nDisheartening Laugh: Heal Adds.\nPit of Despair: Move from void zone.\nLingering Corruption: Dispel.\n\nTANKS\n\nTitanic Smash: Strafe.\nHurl Corruption: Interrupt.\nBurst of Corruption: Move.\nPiercing Corruption: Use cooldown." 
-- Sha of Pride 
L["encounter:71734"] = "++SHA OF PRIDE\n\nINTRO\n\nPlayers have Pride bar, which starts empty. \nPride gained on damage, filling bar. \nWhen full, mind controlled.\n\n+MAIN PHASE\n\nALL\n\nStack behind Boss.\nGift of the Titans buff prevents Pride accrual. \n-Stack for Power of Titans damage buff.\nSelf-Reflection: Move from eruption.\nCorrupted Prison: Stand on orange buttons to free prisoner.\n\nOn Swelling Pride:\nAfter first, spread.\n25% Bursting Pride: Move from void zone.\n50% Projection: Move to Projection marked by arrow.\n75% Aura of Pride: Move away from others.\n100% Overcome: Mind controlled.\nStack after.\n\nManifestation: Two with low corruption move close to soak Last Word.\n\nDPS\n\nKill Adds as priority.\nManifestation's Mocking Blast: Interrupt.\nReflections: AOE.\nPower of the Titans: Use damage cooldowns.\n\nHEALERS\n\nMark of Arrogance: Healer with Gift of Titans buff dispel.\n\nTANKS\n\nWounded Pride: Swap.\nManifestations: Tank.\nMocking Blast: Interrupt.\nReflections: Tank.\n\n +BURN PHASE\n\nAt 30% Pride resets and starts timed filling.\nBoss gains Unleashed raid-wide damage buff.\nHero and burn Boss." 
-- Galakras 
L["encounter:72957"] = "++GALAKRAS\n\nINTRO\n\nTwo phases. First is to capture towers, fighting adds. Second is Boss fight.\n\n+TOWER PHASE\n\nAssigned team takes towers. Rest stay on ground. \nAfter tower captures, shoot Boss with both Turrets simultaneously.\n\nALL\n\nStalkers: Move away.\nFlameslingers: Move from fire.\nWind Reavers: Kill using Turrets.\nPoison Cloud: Move.\nCrusher's Call: Move away.\nArcing Smash: Strafe.\nMuzzle Spray: Strafe.\nShoot: Use defensive cooldown.\n\nDPS\n\nPriorities:\n1. Totems (blue column) and Banners (red column).\n2. Shaman (interrupt heals).\n3. Bonecrushers.\n\nTANKS\n\nTank Adds.\nPoison Cloud: Move.\nBonecrusher: Taunt off Faction Leader.\nProto-Drakes: Face away from raid.\nThranok: Face away from raid.\n\n+BOSS PHASE\n\nALL\n\nMelee stack close behind Boss. \nRanged stack 30 yards behind Boss.\nHero and cooldowns at 40%.\n\nTANKS\n\nFace Boss away.\nSwap on debuff drop." 
-- Iron Juggernaut 
L["encounter:71466"] = "++IRON JUGGERNAUT\n\nINTRO\n\nSingle Boss with two alternating phases.\n\n+ASSAULT PHASE\n\nALL\n\nHero at start.\nSpread behind Boss.\nMortar Cannon: Move from red circle.\nBorer Drill: Avoid earth spikes.\nCrawler Mines: Detonate using mitigation cooldowns.\n\nTANKS\n\nFlame Vents: Face Boss away from raid.\nIgnite Armor: Swap on debuff drop.\nCrawler Mines: Non-aggro Tank detonates.\n\n+SIEGE PHASE\n\nNo tanking needed.\nDemolisher Cannons: Spread to avoid splash.\nCutter Laser: Kite, Avoiding Explosive Tar.\nExplosive Tar: Move away.\nShock Pulse: Stand with obstacle behind to limit knock-back.\nSeismic Activity: Raid heals." 
-- Kor'kron Dark Shaman 
L["encounter:71859"] = "++KOR'KRON DARK SHAMAN\n\nINTRO\n\nTwo Bosses with shared health. \nEach Boss gains powers as health decreases.\n\nALL\n\nToxic Storm: Avoid moving Storm and Tornadoes.\nFoul Stream: Move from green void zone.\nAshen Wall: Move from stationary Adds.\nFalling Ash: Move from red void zone.\n\nDPS\n\nKill mounts first.\nMelee on Haromm.\nRanged on Kardris.\nFoul Geyser: Ranged kill Foul Slimes.\nBloodlust (25%): Hero and cooldowns.\n\nHEALERS\n\nToxic Mist: Heal target.\nFalling Ash: Heal raid.\n\nTANKS\n\nThree Tanks. Two on Haromm. One on Kardris.\nSwipe: Face mounts away from raid.\nHaromm Froststorm Strike: Swap on debuff drop.\nHaromm Ashen Wall: Forms perpendicular to facing. Move away.\nKardris Foul Geyser: Kite Foul Slimes away from raid." 
-- General Nazgrim 
L["encounter:73939"] = "++GENERAL NAZGRIM\n\nINTRO\n\nWarrior Boss with rage bar. Goal is to avoid generating rage. \nUses strongest ability based on rage available. \nAdds summoned in pairs.\n\nALL\n\nHeroic Shockwave: Spread. \nAftershocks: Move from fire lines.\nRavager: Move away from spinning weapon.\n\nDPS\n\nAt start, kill Faithful Adds with AOE.\nDefensive Stance: DO NOT HIT BOSS, except Tanks.\n\nPriorities:\n1. Banners and Totems.\n2. WARSHAMANS (INTERRUPT Chain Heal, Purge Earth Shield).\n3. Arcweavers (Interrupt Magistrike and Arcane Shock).\n4. Assassins (Flares, Stun, Assassin's Mark: Face Add).\n5. Ironblades (Move away on Ironstorm, Ranged kill).\n6. Boss.\n\nHero and damage cooldowns at 10%. \n\nHEALERS\n\nBonecracker: Heal target.\nWar Song: Heal raid.\nBerserker Stance: Heal Tank.\n\nTANKS\n\nStay on Boss.\nSundering Blow: Swap IMMEDIATELY on debuff drop." 
-- Malkorok 
L["encounter:71454"] = "++MALKOROK\n\nINTRO\n\nTwo alternating timed phases. \nMight Phase, rage bar fills. \nBlood Rage Phase, bar empties.\n\n+MIGHT PHASE\n\nALL\n\nSeismic Slam: Stay SPREAD.\nArcing Smash: Avoid 3 frontal cones.\nBreath of Y'Shaarj: Avoid previous 3 Arcing Smash zones.\nImploding Energy: Soak 3-7 zones, only one player with full shield in each.\nHero at start.\n\nHEALERS\n\nAncient Miasma: Heal players to create and maintain damage shields.\nHeal red and yellow shields, ignore health bars.\nSeismic Slam: Heal target.\nImploding Energy: Heal soakers.\n\nTANKS\n\nTank in center.\nFatal Strike: Swap on debuff drop.\n\n+RAGE PHASE\n\nALL\n\nBlood Rage: STACK on Tanks to share damage.\nDisplaced Energy: Move away from raid." 
-- Spoils of Pandaria 
L["encounter:71889"] = "++SPOILS OF PANDARIA\n\nINTRO\n\nTwo groups enter separate sets of chambers. \nRelease and Kill adds from crates to enable lever to move to next chamber. \nCrates: Lightweight; Stout; Massive; Pandaren.\n\nALL\n\nCrimson Reconstitution: Stand in for heals.\nMatter Scramble: Stand in both beams to disable.\nMogu Rune of Power: Stand on for buff.\nSparks of Life: Move away.\nSet to Blow: Place bombs in vacant area. Move away.\nWindstorm: Avoid tornadoes.\nGusting Bomb: Spread. Avoid void zone.\nThrow Explosives: Spread.\nEncapsulated Pheromone: Avoid clouds.\nKeg Toss: Move from target. Stay spread.\nBreath of Fire: Strafe.\nGusting Crane Kick: Run away.\nPath of Blossoms: Move from charge path. Avoid Blossoms.\nSparks of Life: Avoid.\nReturn to Stone: Avoid Stone Statues. Attack Massive Boss from range.\n\nDPS\n\nBurial Urns: Damage to close. Top priority.\nReturn to Stone: Stay on Massive Boss. Ignore Stone Statues.\nEarthen Shard: Interrupt.\nForbidden Magic: Interrupt.\nHarden Flesh: Interrupt.\nResidue: Purge.\nRage of the Empress: Purge.\nClaw of Burning Anger: Passive damage buff.\n\nHEALERS\n\nPheromone Cloud: Heal raid.\nTorment: Dispel.\nHarden Flesh: Dispel.\nBreath of Fire: Dispel.\nStaff of Resonating Water: Healing wave buff. Face raid.\n\nTANKS\n\nOpen Pandaren Crates first for buffs.\nCircle room, opening all but one Massive crate.\nPickup and tank resulting adds.\nWarcallers: Kite when Enraged.\nCrimson Reconstitution: Move Add from pool.\nMogu Rune of Power: Move Add from rune.\nBlade of the Hundred Steps: Passive Tank stunning and damage buff." 
-- Thok the Bloodthirsty 
L["encounter:71529"] = "++THOK THE BLOODTHIRSTY\n\nINTRO\n\nTwo alternating phases. \nPhase One: \n-Tank and attack Boss. \n-Stack. \n-Ends when majority at 50%.\nPhase Two: \n-Boss fixates. \n-Kite and spread. \n-Free prisoners to end. \n\n+PHASE ONE\n\nALL\n\nStack on Boss's side. \n-Except after Montak, spread, then collapse on Boss on command.\n-Bloodied: Appears at 50% health. Triggers next phase if stacked.\nTail Lash: Avoid rear.\nDeafening Screech: Stop casting to avoid silence.\nBurning Blood (Third): Move from fire patches.\n\nDPS\n\nHero and cooldowns at start.\nIcy Blood (Second): Destroy ice tombs to free players.\n\nHEALERS\n\nDeafening Screech: Heal raid.\nShock Blast; Corrosive, Icy, Burning Blood: Heal target.\nCorrosive Blood (First): Dispel\n\nTANKS\n\nBreaths: Face Boss away. \nSwap on debuff drops.\n\n+PHASE TWO\n\nALL\n\nFixate: \n-Target kites Boss between markers.\n-Rest spread to sides. \n-Stay away from line connecting markers.\n-Avoid Boss's lethal frontal cone.\n\nDPS\n\nMelee: Jailer.\nRanged: Thok.\n\nTANK\n\nTank Jailer by current prison.\nUse dropped key to open to cause transition.\nOrder: \n-Akolik (DOT).\n-Gorai (ice tombs); \n-Montak (fire patches)." 
-- Seigecrafter Blackfuse
L["encounter:72964"] = "++SIEGECRAFTER BLACKFUSE\n\nINTRO\n\nBoss and Automated Shredders on platform. \nDPS Go to northwest belt to destroy one of three inactive adds. \nTwo remaining appear active on southeast belt.\n\nALL\n\nLaunch Sawblade: Move away from sawblades.\nDeath from Above: Move from impact area.\nSuperheated: Kite beam away from raid. Avoid fire patches. \nCrawler Mine: Fixates on player. Detonates on contact. Slow and kite.\nShockwave Missile: Move into previous ripple to avoid expanding waves.\nMagnetic Crush: Pulls players and sawblades into Electromagnet. Run away, avoiding sawblades.\n\nDPS\n\nPriorities:\n-1. Mines (root, snare, stun).\n-2. Shredder (Only Ranged on Death from Above).\n-3. Boss.\nHero and cooldowns at start.\nTwo alternating belt teams of 2 to 4 players:\n-Priorities:\n--1. Electromagnets.\n--2. Mines.\n-Matter Purification Beam: Avoid using gap in wall.\n\n HEALERS\n\nOverload: Heal raid.\nProtective Frenzy: Heal Tank.\n\nTANKS\n\nOne on Boss by first belt.\nOther on Shredder 35 yards away to avoid heals. \nDamage Shredder with sawblades, fire patches.\nElectrostatic Charge: Swap Boss each time a Shredder dies.\nProtective Frenzy: Use defensive cooldown." 
-- Paragons of the Klaxxi
L["encounter:71152"] = "++PARAGONS OF THE KLAXXI\n\nINTRO\n\nNine Paragons with three active at a time. \nWhen one dies, other two heal and gain 10% Paragon's Purpose buff.  \nNext marked by Ready to Fight joins. \nClicking dead Paragon gives buff.\n\nALL\n\nStay spread always.\nWind-Reaver Death from Above: Move from target area of leap.\nPoisoned-Mind Toxic Injection: Marks players with colors. \n-Red: Move away from others.\n-Blue: 2-3 stack. \n-Yellow: Move away to drop cloud.\nManipulator Sonic Projection: Avoid same radial as another player.\nManipulator Mature Kunchong: Avoid frontal Swipe.\nLucid Fiery Edge: Linked players move away from each other. Others avoid beams.\nLocust Whirling: Faces charge path. Move.\nLocust Hurl Amber: Avoid void zones.\nAmber Scorpion: 1. Claw (damage target); 2. Swipe (frontal cone); 3. Sting (DOT); 4. PRIORITY: PREY (kill Parasite).\nSwarmkeeper Aim: Target knocked back. Form line to target, 5 yards apart, to split damage.\n\nDPS\n\nHero and damage cooldowns at start. \nManipulator Mesmerize: Damage Hungry Kunchong 30% to stop Devour.\nManipulator Thick Shell: Do not attack.\nManipulator Molt: Kill Mature Kunchong.\nBloodseeker Bloodletting: Kill Bloods.\nPrime Encase in Amber: Kill Amber Block.\nDissector Amber Parasites: Focus kill one at a time.\n\nOrder (Kill - Appearance - Tank):\n-Dissector Rik'kal - 1 - 1\n-Bloodseeker Skeer - 2 - 2\n-Prime Korven - 5 - X (2)\n-Swarmkeeper Hisek - 3 - 0\n-Poisoned-Mind Xaril - 7 - 1\n-Manipulator Kaz'tik - 8 - 0\n-Locust Ka'roz - 4 - X (Swap)\n-Lucid Iyyokuk - 6 - 0\n-Wind-Reaver Kil'ruk - 9 - 2\n\nHEALERS\n\nWind-Reaver Gouge/Mutilate: Heal Tank. \nPrime Shield Bash/Vicious Assault: Heal Tank.\nLucid Diminish: Heal target. Keep raid above 25%.\nSwarmkeeper Multi-shot: Heal target.\nDissector Amber Scorpion: Heal target.\nDissector Amber Parasite: Heal target.\n\nTANKS\n\nTank One: Bloodseeker and Wind-Reaver.\nTank Two: Dissector and Poisoned-Mind.\nNo Tank: Manipulator, Lucid, Swarmkeeper.\nPoisoned-Mind Caustic Blood: Block using active mitigation to avoid Explosion at 10 stacks.\nDissector Injection: Block using active mitigation to avoid Parasites.\nWind-Reaver Gouge/Mutilate: Use defensive cooldown in advance.\nPrime: Shield Bash/Vicious Assault: Use defensive cooldown in advance.\nPrime: Face away from raid.\n\n+BUFFS\n\nALL\n\nManipulator Master of Puppets: Summon damage minion.\nDissector Mad Scientist - Summon Scorpion.\n\nDPS\n\nWind-Reaver Reave: Damaging leap. Disables Parasite's Thick Shell.\nLocust Strong Legs: Jump to platform. Throw damaging amber. Breaks Amber Blocks.\nBloodseeker Bloodthirsty: Healing orbs. Walk over for heal.\nSwarmkeeper Compound Eye: Ranged damage buff. Use at max range.\n\nHEALERS\n\nLucid Ingenious: Copies heals to same class or race.\nPoisoned-Mind Volatile Poultice: Stores heals on target.\n\nTANKS\n\nPrime Master of Amber: Target immunity.\n\nMACRO\n\n/targetexact Amber" 
-- Garrosh Hellscream
L["encounter:71865"] = "++GARROSH HELLSCREAM\n\nINTRO\n\nFour phase fight.\nPhase 1: Ends at 10%. Adds.\nTransition Phase: Lasts 1 minute. Alternates with Phase 2. Boss gains energy.\nPhase 2: Heals to full. Ends at 10%. Uses energy to Empower spells.\nPhase 3: Heals to 25%. Ends at death. All spells are Empowered.\n\n+PHASE 1\n\nEnds at 10%. \n\nALL\n\nRanged spread far behind Boss.\nMelee stack close behind Boss. \nIron Star: \n-Move from path. \n-Stay away from impact wall. \n-Knock Adds into path.\n\nDPS\nWarbringers: AOE.\nRiders: Single-target. Priority kill. \nRider's Ancestral Chain Heal: INTERRUPT.\nRider's Chain Lightning: DO NOT INTERRUPT.\nDesecrate: Ranged kill weapon. Use DOTs.\nSiege Engineer: Designated Ranged kill one only. \nUse Hero and damage cooldowns at the start.\n\nHEALERS\n\nHellscream's Warsong: Heal Add Tank.\n\nTANKS\n\nOne on Garrosh. \nOther on Warbringers and Riders.\nIron Star: Move Adds into path if no knock-back.\n\n+REALM PHASE\n\nLasts 1 minute.\nIn Serpent and Crane, split into two groups.\nStack and kill Adds.\nPop bubbles. \nGarrosh: Attack stop energy siphon.\nAnnihilate: Constantly move to stay behind.\n\n+PHASE 2\n\nHeals to full.\nEnds at 10%.\nEnergy Empowers spells.\n\nALL\n\nRanged spread far behind Boss.\nMelee stack close behind Boss. \nWhirling Corruption: All stack far behind Boss. \nDesecrated Weapon: Avoid.\n\nDPS\n\nDesecrate: Ranged kill weapon. Use DOTs.\nEmpowered Whirling Corruption (25%): \n-Taunt minions apart.\n-Kill with single-target attacks.\nTouch of Y'Saarj: \n-INTERRUPT AND STUN. \n-Damage to 20%.\nEmpowered Touch (50%): INTERRUPT ONLY.\n\nHEALERS\n\nEmpowered Gripping Despair (100%): Heal Off-Tank on debuff drop.\n\nTANKS\n\nTank Boss in center.\nGripping Despair: Swap on debuff drop.\n\n+PHASE 3\n\nEnds at death.\nAll spells Empowered.\nEmpowered Desecrate (75%): Cannot kill weapon. Move away and ignore.\nEmpowered Gripping Despair (100%): \n-Tanks use defensive cooldown on debuff drop.\n-Healers heal Off-Tank.\nEmpowered Whirling Corruption: Tank Minions. Do not kill.\nUse Hero and damage cooldowns." 

-- Added by Linty Druid

L["encounter:78714"] ="++Priority\nSorcerers -> Kargath\n \n++General\n \nIf you are the target of [Berserker Rush] run behind the [Flame Pillar] and [Flame Jet] to stop his attack. Avoid standing in the [Flame Jet].\n \n++Battle in the stands group:\n \nAfter [Chain Hurl], Stands group run into the boss  and all other player run away. Stands group will be transported to the stands and should kill the [Drunken Bileslingers] and [Iron Bombers]"

L["encounter:77404"]="Raid splits into four groups.\n \n++Tank Group:\n Tight Stack and faces boss away from raid, Swap at 3 or 4 stacks of [The cleaver] or [The Tenderizer].\n \n++Close Range Groups A and B \n Keeps within DPS range and in a tightly stacked group. 1 player in each group is the 'Floater', and only one of these should be with  their group at any one time (making their group the largest).\nThe largest group will be inflicted with [Gushing Wounds] and at 2 stacks on one group the floater should leave the group.  The 2nd floater should join their group, attracting [gushing wounds] (rinse and repeat).\nGroups A and B must have the largest number of players and have an equal number.\nRestack when you are thrown away from boss.\n \n++Raged Group:  The majority of healers and ranged player would ideally be in this group and would stay at max range.\nSome ranged and healers may have to be part of groups A & B to ensure the correct player balance."

L["encounter:78491"] ="++Priority\nFungal Flesh Eaters -> Iron Warmasters -> Iron Blood Mages -> Iron Flame Technicians -> Other Trash -> Brackenspore\n \n++General\nStand in [Living Mushrooms] and [Rejuvenating Mushroom] if you can. Get in range of [Living Mushroom] for [Infesting Spores] cast by boss to survive. Avoid standing in the [Creeping Moss].\n \n++Creeping Moss:\n Two DPS, ideally hunters must take staffs and use flame-thrower to destroy creeping moss.\n \n++Tanks:\n  Face boss away from raid. Switch on 3 stacks of [Rot]. Taunt [Fungal Flesh Eaters]\n \nHealers: Keep at least one living mushroom alive at any one time (by healing it)."

L["encounter:78948"] ="++Oro, Lokk, and Rokkaa\nWhenever one of these trash reaches 20% health, he begins to cast [Reconstitution].\nKill him before he competes the 20 second cast or he will be healed fully over 10 seconds. Priority is to kill Oro.  Stand in the circles with the yellow arrows and get out of the brown circles. Keep Lokk and Rokkaa apart, so one tank will tank oro with one of the other elemental and the second holding the last elemental.\n \n++Tectus\nYou can only attack tectus when  he is casting [Tectonic Upheaval] and and each successful cast restores 20% health.  if you are targeted for [Earthen Pillar] move to the edge of the area and place the pillar outside the raid. If you are targeted for [Crystalline Barrage] move away from the raid group.\n \n++Shards and Motes\nShards and Motes  have the same abilities as Tectus.  Motes can be killed immediately.\n \n++Sequence:\n [orr/lokk/rokkaa] -> [Tectus] -> [Shard 1] -> [Motes 1-4] -> [Shard 2] -> [Motes 5-8]"


L["encounter:79015"] = "Primary Mechanic: Nullification Barrier/Rune of Nullification\n\nKo'ragh starts with a Barrier that absorbs magic damage. Once broken, he summons a Rune of Nullification and charges a new barrier. One player can step on the Rune and charge their own Barrier, but they take heavy damage while doing so.\n\nThese Barriers can be used to soak Overflowing Energy orbs that spawn every 30 seconds. Orb spawn rate increases over time and Barriers deplete as they take orb damage, so multiple players will need to charge Barriers.\n\nOther mechanics\n  - Suppression Field: Void zone that damages and silences. Avoid.\n  - Volatile Anomaly: Adds; position inside Suppression field void zone to silence.\n  - Expel Magic (Arcane): Tank swap.\n  - Expel Magic (Fire): Raidwide damage, spread out.\n  - Expel Magic (Frost); Frost orb, avoid.\n  - Expel Magic (Shadow): Raidwide heal prevention effect, use healing cooldowns to power through quickly."
L["encounter:77428"] = "Primary Mechanic: Displacement, Fortification, Replication\n\nAt 90%, 55%, and 25% HP, Mar'gok will activate these Runestones in turn, granting him power which empowers his five primary abilities. Destructive Resonance is used constantly throughout the fight; the rest are used in order.\n\nThis is a very complex fight, so I will go into more detail of each ability in order.\n\n++Ability 1: Destructive Resonance++\nA debuff is placed on a ranged player; once it expires, a mine is placed at that player's feet that persists for one minute. Once it activates, triggering it will do near-fatal personal damage and heavy raid-wide damage.\n  - Destructive Resonance (Displacement): Mine grows bigger before expiring.\n  - Destructive Resonance (Fortification): Mine persists for two minutes, instead of one.\n  - Destructive Resonance (Replication): Mine will create two additional mines when it expires.\n\n++Ability 2: Branded++\nA debuff that jumps from player to player in the raid every 4 seconds, damaging the player it jumped from. Starts with 12 stacks, increases damage and loses range for every jump. Players receiving Branded with 8 stacks or fewer should move away from the raid to force it to expire.\n\nBranded (Displacement): Players with Branded cannot move more than 10 yards. Raid must move away from player to allow it to clear.\n  - Branded (Fortification): Range loss from jumping decreased. Player should not attempt to force it to expire until 3-4 stacks; players will take very heavy damage from jumps at low stack counts.\n  - Branded (Replication): Two stacks of Branded go out; strategy is otherwise unchanged.\n\n++Ability 3: Arcane Aberration++\nAdd picked up by off-tank that does light raidwide AoE damage.\n  - Aberration (Displacement): Aberration has a knockback when it dies. Position accordingly.\n  - Aberration (Fortification): Aberration has a much larger healthpool, and becomes immune to CC. No change to strategy.\n  - Aberration (Replication): Aberration will spawn several Arcane Remnants when it dies, which must be AoE'd.\n\n++Ability 4: Mark of Chaos++\nAn 8 second debuff applied to the current tank which kills anyone within 35 yards on expiration. The debuffed tank should run away from the raid, the offtank should taunt, and all raid members run away from the debuffed tank.\n  - Mark of Chaos (Displacement): Affected tank is randomly teleported when debuff is applied.\n  - Mark of Chaos (Fortification): Tank is rooted. Raid must use movement speed abilities to run away.\n  - Mark of Chaos (Replication): When Mark of Chaoe explodes, 8 highly-damaging orbs fly out from the tank. Avoid.\n\n++Ability 5: Force Nova++\nA wave that emanates from Mar'gok and does heavy damage. Players should run towards Mar'gok to cross wave faster and reduce damage taken.\n  - Force Nova (Displacement): Nova will slow crossers, requiring a movement-speed buff to reduce damage taken.\n  - Force Nova (Fortification): Three Novas will occur over 16 seconds. Damage reduction or healing cooldowns may be necessary.\n  - Force Nova (Replication): Players will replicate damage taken by Force Nova to other players within 4 yards. Spread out while crossing.\n\n++Intermissions: Adds++\nThere are two intermissions at 55% and 20% HP where Mar'gok is unattackable and adds spawn. Kill adds in this order:\n  - Gorian Warmage: 2 per intermission, untankable, constantly casts spells at random raid members.\n  - Volatile Anomaly: Multiple spawn during intermission, should be picked up by tanks and kept away from Warmages. Explode for raidwide when destroyed, so should not be AoE'd. \n  - Gorian Reaver (intermission 2): Has a cone attack (Devastating Shockwave) and forces a tank swap (Kick to the Face)."
L["encounter:78238"] = "Primary Mechanic: Blaze, Phemos, 100 energy\n\nPhemos will throw his weapons down and cast Quake (unavoidable raidwide damage) then Blaze, igniting walls of fire throughout the room. Tanks should move bosses behind weapons to avoid the majority of the fire walls.\n\nOther mechanics:\n  - Pulverize: Pol, 100 energy. Spread out and avoid Pulverize zones.\n  - Whirlwind: Phemos, 33 energy. Avoid, tank should move him away from raid.\n  - Enfeebling Roar: Phemos, 66 energy. Stack on Phemos to split damage.\n  - Shield Charge: Pol, 33 energy. Avoid boss's Charge.\n  - Interrupting Shout: Pol, 66 energy. Stop casting.\n  - Double Slash/Shield Bash: Increased damage by casting boss. Tanks should be aware of increased damage and use cooldowns as necessary."

--Black Rock Foundry

L["encounter:77325"] = "General: Phase 1: move behind a Debris Pile if targeted by Marked for Death ; avoid the Throw Slag Bombs; avoid the Molten Slag ; move away from the locations of the falling debris caused by Demolition. Same as 1 except: move behind a Siegemaker if targeted by Marked for Death;spread out at least 6 yards apart. Phase 3: if targeted by Attach Slag Bombs, move out of the raid, ideally close to the edge of the platform; stay away from Slag Holes or Slag Craters; if targeted by Marked for Death, move so that there are no other players in front of or behind you, relative to Blackhand's location.\nTanks: During Phases One and Two, the off-tank should taunt Blackhand when Shattering Smash knocks back his tank. During Phase One, tank Blackhand close to the Molten Slag. During Phase Two, Blackhand's tank should aim at being knocked up onto the ledge of the room, where they should damage and kill some of the Iron Soldiers located there. During Phase Three, tank Blackhand close to the edge of the platform, and kite him away from his most recent Slag Crater.\nDPS: In Phase 2, ranged DPS players should prioritise killing the Siegemakers, when their Blackiron Plating buff is removed; a few melee DPS players should enter the Shattering Smash radius and be knocked up onto the ledge of the room, where they should kill the Iron Soldiers located there."
L["encounter:76865"] = "Ranged raid members must be spread out at all times except for the first 15% of the boss' health. Melee players should spread out temporarily when Rend and Tear is being cast.\n Tanks: Perform a tank switch throughout the fight (except for the first 15% of the boss' health), to deal with Rend and Tear, Crush Armor, and Seared Flesh, respectively. Tank the boss near the place where the Pack Beasts enter the fight, and make sure to pick up and tank all the Pack Beasts.\nDPS: Priority: Heavy Spears->Pack Beasts->Boss, also Against Cruelfang, remove the enrage effects from the boss and the Pack Beasts."
L["encounter:76814"] = "General: Casters and healers should be spread out throughout the encounter. Avoid coming in contact with the fire lines. If a Cinder Wolf is fixating on you, kite him. If you are targeted by Molten Torrent, move into a group of players. If you are targeted by Blazing Radiance, move away from other raid members. Move out of the areas on the floor where Magma Monsoon will land. Tanks: Oone tank takes Ka'graz, while the other tank takes Aknor Steelbringer and faces him away from the rest of the raid. When the Cinder Wolves are up, one tank should always tank the wolf that is Overheated. Each time the wolves swap roles (the other wolf becomes Overheated), the tanks should perform a tank switch between Ka'graz and the newly Overheated wolf. After Ka'graz finishes casting Firestorm, the two tanks will have to perform a tank switch to handle her temporary Flamefury ability. \nHealers:Dispel any players who are affected by Singe.\nDPS: Priority: Cinder Wolves (die together) -> Aknor"
L["encounter:76906"] = "General: During full length add trains, the raid splits in to two full groups (track 1 and track 4). Avoid being hit by any of the trains that enter the room. Avoid the Prototype Pulse Grenade Icon Prototype Pulse Grenade void zones. Be prepared to move to your assigned part of the room when the raid splits up into two groups.\nTanks: Perform a tank switch on Operator Thogar to handle the Enkindle DoT. Pick up all of the adds that come in on the trains.\nDPS: Priority Firemenders->Men-at-Arms->Gunnery Sergeants(ranged only)->Other Adds -> Boss"
L["encounter:76809"] = "During Phase One, spread out at least 5 yards apart to avoid taking additional damage from Electrocution . If you are affected by Bomb , go to the nearest Heat Regulator and detonate your bomb.\nDuring Phase Two, if you are Fixate on by a Slag Elemental, move on top of a Primal Elementalist. Make sure to interrupt Firecallers' Cauterize Wounds.During Phase Three, make sure to take such position as to minimise the amount of space that the Melt void zones take up.\nTanks: During Phase One, each tank should handle the adds that spawn in one half of the room (as assigned). When tanking Security Guards, keep them away from the Bellows Operators.During Phase Two, tank the Security Guards away from the other adds.\nDuring Phase Three, perform a tank switch on Heart of the Mountain when the current tank has 3 stacks of Heat.\nHealers: During Phase One, players who have bombs will take damage when they detonate them, so they will require additional healing. During Phase Two, players on whom the Slag Elementals Fixate will likewise require additional healing. Save cooldowns for phase 3.\nDPS: Priority: Phase 1 = Feldspar->Engineers & Operators; Phase 2 = Slag Elementals->Elementalists; Phase 3: Heart of mountain."
L["encounter:76974"] = "General: When a player is targeted by Body Slam Icon Body Slam, move away from them to avoid being debuffed. When the conveyor belts become active, make sure to avoid the Searing Plates or the metal presses from Pulverized. Stay away from the ends of the conveyor belts.\n Tanks: Each tank should pick up one of the bosses. When a tank's stacks of Shattered Vertebrae get too high, perform a tank switch. Tank the two bosses close to each other. When Body Slam is being cast, move away from the melee group."
L["encounter:76877"] = "General: Split up into two groups of roughly equal size, located on opposite sides of Gruul, in melee range.  Whenever Petrifying Slam is cast, make sure to move at least 8 yards away from raid members affected by Petrification.\nTanks: Perform a regular tank switch to handle the debuffs applied by Inferno Slice and Overwhelming Blows. When tanking Gruul, tank him at least 10 yards away from any other raid members (including the other tank), and facing him away from anyone else. When Inferno Slice is about to be cast, move into one of the two groups of players so that they split the damage from Inferno Slice, and then quickly move out again. Alternate\n Healers: Be prepared for sustained raid-wide damage during Phase Two.\nDPS: Kill!!!"
L["encounter:77692"] = "General: When the boss casts Rune of Grasping Earth, move so that each raid member is located on top of a small orange rune, with no rune having more than one player on top of it. Players with damage immunities can stay out to give the rest of the players more runes to work with. Avoid the sonic discs from Reverberations, the cone attack from Rippling Smash, the giant stone hands from Rune of Crushing Earth, and move away from the boss when Slam is being cast. Tanks: Stand on top of each other (to split the damage of Fists of Stone Icon Fists of Stone), and perform a tank switch to handle Warped Armor."
L["encounter:77182"] = "During Phase One: Interrupt as many casts of Blackrock Barrage as possible. Avoid the Retched Blackrock void zones (ranged) and the Explosive Shard (melee).\nDuring Phase Two: Avoid being hit by Oregorger. Do not lose line of sight to the healers.\nTank: Perform a tank switch on the boss for each Acid Torrent Icon Acid Torrent cast. The tank currently tanking Oregorger must make sure that they are the closest player to the boss.\n Healers:Heal the raid-wide damage from Acid Torrent. Make sure that the tank who is being hit by Acid Torrent has some damage mitigation cooldown active, or otherwise be prepared for high raid-wide damage.\n DPS: During Phase Two, DPS and quickly kill Ore Crates"
L["encounter:77557"] = "General: Platform: Be spread out at least 8 yards apart to minimise the damage; Move away from other players (and towards the edge of the platform) when you are targeted by Rapid Fire; Move in front of Marak the Blooded if you are targeted by Blood Ritual; Move in between Admiral Gar'an and the player targeted by Penetrating Shot, in order to split the damage;Players targeted by Bloodsoaked Heartseeker must move away from one another. Ship: Spread out around Uktar to minimise the damage from Grapeshot Blast; Constantly move out of the void zones, trying to conserve space.\nTanks: One tank should take Sorka, the other tank should take Marak. Gar'an does not have a threat table and does not melee, but she can be taunted to have her focus her damage on tanks for limited amounts of time. Whenever a boss jumps to a ship, one of the two tanks must use a chain to go to the ship as well, and tank the mob(s) present there.\nDPS: DPS the 3 bosses in a balanced way, following the priority given to you by the raid leader. If you are jumping on the ship, prioritise the adds over the mini bosses, and be sure to interrupt Battle Medic Rogg as much as possible."
--World Bosses

L["encounter:81535"] = "Do not stand in front of Tarlna to avoid his frontal cone, Colossal Blow. Healers should also be ready to use cooldowns for the raid damage portion of this ability.\nStay spread for, and be ready to heal people who are afflicted by,  Savage Vines.\NJust like Yalnu in The Everbloom, Tarlna will spawn a field of sproutlings during  Genesis. Run over them to stamp them out.\nIf the sproutlings are not stamped out by running over them, they will evolve intoGiant Lasher. These adds cast  Lasher Venom and should be killed quickly.\nIn addition to those adds, Tarlna also spawns Untamed Mandragora which should be tanked and killed. They spawn pools of venom through  Noxious Spit. Don't stand in those!"
L["encounter:81252"] = "Do not stand in front of Drov during  Colossal Slam and healers should be ready to use cooldowns during this for the raid damage portion of the ability.\nRaid-wide damage also happens during  Giga Smash, so use cooldowns or personals then as welll.\nDrov will periodically cast  Call of Earth which awakens Frenzied Rumbler. These Goren adds should be killed."
L["encounter:87493"] = "Much like her fight in Skyreach, you will have to watch out for the Piles of Ash that the boss creates.\nAvoid the Piles of Ash due to  Blaze of Glory. This will reignite them if you are within 5 yards of a pile.\nWhen the boss flies in the air, healers should be ready to heal the random raid damage from  Loose Quills.\nThroughout the fight,  Blood Feather will cause Rukhmar to spawn phoenixes that fixate on players. Run away from the phoenix that is fixated on you.\nPlayers should kill each others phoenixes away from the Piles of Ash so they do not reignite.\nTanks will need to tank swap due to  Pierced Armor and  Sharp Beak.\nEnergized Phoenixes fixate on random players, but Depleted Phoenixes can be tanked normally.\nTanks should face the boss away from the raid at all times due to  Solar Breath.\nHealers will need to keep on top of the constant raid damage from  Solar Radiatiown"

-- Added by LintyDruid

--Auchindoun

L["encounter:75839"] = "Move away from Hallowed Ground as the light spawns. Everyone hide behind shield (LOS from boss) during Consecrated Light, but dont stack behind it too soon so you can avoid dropping Hallowed Ground back there.\nHEROIC CHANGES: Boss can now detonate Hallowed Ground, so avoid being near them at all costs. You will be able to visually see their range. Healing is easy IF everyone stays away from Hallowed Ground."
L["encounter:76177"] = "Move into the center Soul Vessel bubble that the boss summons to avoid taking damage. Yes, it really hurts. Interrupt Mind Spikes and casts from adds, AOE adds, healers cleanse Shadow Word: Pain when possible.\nHEROIC CHANGES: Healers dispel the stacking Crusader Strike debuff from the tank as often as possible. Tank damage is high when adds are out, especially if not interrupted. May want to tanking magus add in Soul Vessel if Arcane Bomb is blowing up."
L["encounter:77734"] = "Changes at 75% to a random warlock spec. With any, move out of all AOE, cleanse debuffs (NOT Unstable Affliction!), interrupt when possible. If targeted with Seed of Malevolence, run away from rest of party to avoid spreading it.\nHEROIC CHANGES: Boss summons an Abyssal, which fixates and chases them. They have high health and can be CCed, so kite them instead of killing them. Malevolence will bloom upon expiration, try to drop it at the edge of the room to be kind to the kiters."
--Bloodmail Slag Mines

L["encounter:74787"] = "Fairly straightforward, dont stand in Magma Barrage. He summons both a rock and fire elemental. Rock stuns, fire casts. Healer dispels debuff or it jumps to another. Ogre summons actual boss, who does AOE stun. Tank adds and avoid stuns.\nHEROIC CHANGES: Debuff for healer to dispel (Dancing Flames) hits two targets instead of one, initially. Dispel quickly and roll heals on the afflicted. Glyphing your cleanse is helpful."
L["encounter:74366"] = "Fairly straightforward, dont stand in Magma Barrage. He summons both a rock and fire elemental. Rock stuns, fire casts. Healer dispels debuff or it jumps to another. Ogre summons actual boss, who does AOE stun. Tank adds and avoid stuns.\nHEROIC CHANGES: Debuff for healer to dispel (Dancing Flames) hits two targets instead of one, initially. Dispel quickly and roll heals on the afflicted. Glyphing your cleanse is helpful."
L["encounter:75768"] = "Fiery Boulder! Boss rolls them, avoid them or die. Run towards boss during Heat Wave since it pushes back. Burning slag places fire. A LOT of fire. Dont stand in it, dont get stunned by boulders, dont get pushed back into fire.\nHEROIC CHANGES: The Fiery Boulder returns along the same path that it rolled out, so avoid it coming up from behind you. Boss radiates decreased cast-spead aura, preventing stacking in melee range for casters/healers."
L["encounter:74790"] = "Tons of AOE damage. Focus kill Slag before they walk to the kilns or youll get more AOE damage. Interrupt bosss Molten Blast, dispel his Molten Core. If he casts 3x Molten Blast, use defensive/healing CDs on Molten Barrage.\nHEROIC CHANGES: Healers dispel Flame Buffet, a stacking debuff. Prioritize highest stacks of debuff first. If you have debuff, fire on ground is more deadly, must avoid!"
--The Everbloom

L["encounter:83894"] = "Three bosses, should generally kill Gola>Telu>Dulhu. Can only tank Dulhhu, so tank near current main target. Avoid projected knockback from boss and thorns on ground, interrupt Golas casts, dispel mobs with Briarskin and Rapid Tides.\nHEROIC CHANGES: Gola and Telu gain an immunity to interrupts for 8sec after being interrupted, so time appropriately. Interrupt Golas Revitalizing waters and Telus Bramble Patch. Keep offensively dispelling." --**
L["encounter:82682"] = "During trash gauntlet, focus Bursters down to avoid AOE dmg. During boss, she eats Pale Ones and heals so stun/CC/kill them further away before focusing back on boss. Try not to let them consume poison clouds or they will do a lot of damage.\nHEROIC CHANGES: Harder, faster, stronger. No notable changes to heroic version."
L["encounter:84550"] = "Has three specs: Fire, Frost, Arcane. Control when she phases by interrupting Parasitic Growth. Jump over flame rings in Fire, move away from blizzard in Frost. Interrupt Fireball, Frostbolt, Arcane Burst. AOE heals on Arcane Blossom.\nHEROIC CHANGES: Interrupting Parasitic Growth spawns a Spore Image. Cant kill it, so interrupt as little as possible. If not interrupted, she also gains a damage buff. Effects from one phase will persist for remainder of fight. Dispels important."
L["encounter:81522"] = "Cycles between two phases. 1st, dance around vines that follow players. Boss does frontal cone, lots of damage, DPS should not stand in front. 2nd, boss takes extra damage until four globs hit him, must kill water adds to keep damage buff. Tank adds.\nHEROIC CHANGES: During both phases, boss casts bolts at players that create void zones to NOT stand in. Vines also follow players in second phase."
L["encounter:83864"] = "NPC mages help DPS adds and boss. If group DPS is low, break mages free of Entanglement. Trample sproutlings during Genesis cast. Tank gather adds, use CDs when lots of sproutlings bc of stacking bleed. Everyone sidestep Colossal Blows.\nHEROIC CHANGES: Ylanu now casts Entanglement on players, too. Break part members and NPCs out of it, players being priority because it does heavy damage until broken."
--Grimrail Depot

L["encounter:80005"] = "Move away from Snares, avoid standing in path of spears, dont stand in energy pools when drake flies over. Drake breath covers part of the car in energy pools, so be mindful of path and move accordingly.\nHEROIC CHANGES: Boss marks a party member and throws an explosive spear. Move away from party member, spread out to avoid having to move too often. Move while being targeted to avoid damage."
L["encounter:77803"] = "Rocketspark flies around, Borka does frontal cone. Aim Borka at Rocketspark so his dashes interrupt Rockets barrage. Beware of all of the markers on the ground, avoid being in path of Borkas dash. Borka enrages after Rocket dies, use CDs.\nHEROIC CHANGES: Borkas ground slam now interrupts casting. Healers and casters should target or focus Borka to time their spellcasts accordingly." --**
L["encounter:79545"] = "Lots of AOE, avoid stacking until boss hits 60% and goes in cannon. Tank gets many adds, DPS pop CDs and kill Boomers/Grenadiers first, attack cannon btw waves. Loot grenades, use on adds. Loot shells, use on Blackrock Turrets; break cannon LOS on fire.\nHEROIC CHANGES: Cannon fires slag, covering 2/3rds of car in fire. Move to unaffected segment of train, make sure to LOS Suppressive Fire ASAP. New add, Gunner, tank facing away from party so shrapnel doesnt hit. Loot shrapnel, use on turrets, kill adds."

--Iron Docks

L["encounter:81305"] = "Have to attack wolf first, who lunges, slows, and puts a bleed on someone. He can howl and heal allies. Kill wolf, stay out of fire arrows, tank/kill adds. Boss fears if attacked during red shield (Reckless Provocation).\nHEROIC CHANGES: Boss gets off mount at 50%, have to deal with both wolf and boss simultaneously. Pop hero/lust, focus wolf down. Healers pop CDs during wolfs Savage Mauling."
L["encounter:80816"] = "Three bosses, no shared health. Emberblade: Avoid dash, avoid lava waves. Nox: Spread out for chain lightning, avoid being surrounded by traps, avoid bomb being thrown. Dugru: Healers dispel Tainted Blood, switch from targets with blood shield.\nHEROIC CHANGES: Harder, faster, stronger. No notable changes to heroic version. Focus Dugru first to try and avoid any blood shields."
L["encounter:79852"] = "Hit him during Feeding Frenzy to interrupt his heal. Adrenalized Roar does ~50k damage, which is significant, and his whirl hits melee in range. Occasionally charges and opens a cage, stun/kill wolves and skyterrors, avoiding acid puddles.\nHEROIC CHANGES: When wolves are together, they do 25% more damage, so beware and kill them quickly using stuns whenever possible. Feeding Frenzy requires more damage to break."
L["encounter:83612"] = "Tank Skulloc, kill first orc. Move away from group if have Rapid Fire. Kill orc, boss knocks back. Must move forward and duck behind boxes during barrages. Dash forward after last box to stop barrage, ignore add and just finish killing Skulloc.\nHEROIC CHANGES: No new mechanics for heroic, but first orc is less likely to die before first barrage, so you will have to duck. Dont forget to move away if youre targeted with Rapid Fire. Still ignore last add if DPS is high and kill boss." --**
--Shadowmoon Burial Grounds

L["encounter:75509"] = "Defiled Spirits are priority, dont let them hit the boss! Can be stunned/snared, not rooted. Dont touch purple runes at all. Touch white Lunar Purity for buff during Dark Eclipse to survive, dont have to stand in. Mitigate Deathspike, avoid Daggerfall.\nHEROIC CHANGES: No changes to heroic version, but Defiled Spirits are harder to kill. Coordinate stuns and snares as much as possible. Two Daggerfalls spawn instead of one, so avoid standing in them."
L["encounter:75452"] = "Dodge bosss Body Slam. If you get knocked off, use water jets to get back up. When boss inhales, dash away or he deals big damage. Avoid puddles till inhale, then stand in if you need to be slowed down till after inhale. AOE heals during big exhale.\nHEROIC CHANGES: After first inhale, two worms join fight that can also Body Slam and spit. Kill worms ASAP and return to boss."
L["encounter:76407"] = "Tough fight. Point Malevolence away from party. Ranged move away from Omen of Death asap, melee be careful of bones and avoid them. Bones spawn in the four cardinal directions; kill one and stand on that side to create clear space to stand in.\nHEROIC CHANGES: No changes to heroic version, but positioning Omen of Death is more important because it deals higher damage. Damage to kill bones higher as well, so be on top of switching targets and focus one down."
L["encounter:75829"] = "Repeats two phases. In void phase, everyone defeat own soul and loot corpse to grant returned soul. Avoid mounds or they spawn adds, move boss from void zones so melee can DPS. Tank use mitigation when boss casts Void Blast. Spread out to avoid vortexes.\nHEROIC CHANGES: No changes to heroic version, but avoid vortexes ASAP to avoid unnecessary damage. Healers prioritize trying to top everyone off before phased into soul realm, use damage reduction CDs in soul realm."
--Skyreach

L["encounter:75954"] = "Lots of movement! Sidestep Piercing Rush. Avoid the spinning chakram and moving line of them. After several, he will cast four walls of cyclones that rotate. Must walk between the walls as they move, avoiding chakrams.\nHEROIC CHANGES: Chakrams last longer. After cyclones, a beam of light appears on a player. That player needs to move to the edge of the platform to drop the Lens Flare puddles out of the way. Healers note moving allies and move accordingly."
L["encounter:76141"] = "Tank can sidestep Smash. Boss will occasionally cast Burst, which may need lots of AOE healing CDs, and hits harder every time he casts it for a soft enrage. Stand in beams to block boss heals, but move out if taking too much damage for your healer.\nHEROIC CHANGES: Harder, faster, stronger. Will have two healing beams to manage instead of one and they heal for more, so coordination is important. Burst hurts a lot more."
L["encounter:76379"] = "Boss summons Solar Flare that fixates. Focus add down, when they die they explode and leave ashes. Do not kill additional adds near it or they resurrect. Tank must be in melee range of boss at all times or boss Screeches and does a lot of AOE.\nHEROIC CHANGES: About every 60sec, the boss sprays Quills. Everyone but tank, who must stay in melee range, can LOS the Quills behind the center pillar. Manage the Solar Flares, careful to not kill them next to each other or they respawn."
L["encounter:76266"] = "Stay near center of platform, Zealots will pick up a player and try to drop them over the edge. Stun/snare/root and kill the Zealot ASAP. Move away from center if targeted with Lens Flare. Interrupt and kill Shield Constructs to avoid shield.\nHEROIC CHANGES: Harder, faster, stronger. Positioning Lens Flare pools is important to avoid Zealot flight paths. Zealots take longer to kill."
--Upper Blackrock Spire

L["encounter:76413"] = "Boss stands in middle, dps boss while avoiding orbs that circuits around room. When lightning tethers to a trap, ranged run to trap and release it. Players stay on platform unless disabling traps or will take heavy damage. Tanks use mitigate during melee.\nHEROIC CHANGES: Spikes on floor push/pull, making deactivating traps a pain. Use speed CDs when necessary. Thunder from activated traps more deadly, players should coordinate which traps they will be releasing to avoid confusion."
L["encounter:76021"] = "Face adds away from party and side-step Eruption. Interrupt bosss Debilitation Fixation. Move away from poison pools, but try not to LOS your healer. Offensively dispel bosss serum buff. Focus adds down before boss.\nHEROIC CHANGES: Boss puts toxic fumes on party member, which AOE damages nearby players. Move away from people with the debuff. It can be cleansed by anyone who can cleanse poisons."
L["encounter:79912"] = "Kill trash waves for boss to come out. Dodge skyreavers breath and spit, side-step Tharbeks charge. Avoid axe, DPS should stay behind skyreaver. Ranged DPS dot the flying hatchlings. Use damage reduction if you have Iron Axe debuff.\nHEROIC CHANGES: Tank damage is high because boss dismounts at 50% and both skyreaver and boss are active. Same abilities, also summons four guards when boss is at 30% health. Tank pick up fast or they hurt, can also be stunned or otherwise CCed."
L["encounter:76585"] = "Boss spits and sets fire to portions of bridge that disorient and heavily damage players. Watch where boss is facing during Engulfing Fire and run to opposite direction to avoid. Gather whelplings, AOE down. Avoid fire puddles. Dispel boss enrage.\nHEROIC CHANGES: No real changes to heroic, but Engulfing Flames is less predictable. Boss enrage hits harder, make sure to try and dispel if you can or pop hero/lust to push through it."
L["encounter:77120"] = "Boss puts cyclone on someone  kite it away from the rest of the party. Hurls blade that ricochets, spread out. At 60%, she gets on drake and adds come out. Avoid fire on bridge. After 40sec, boss comes back and resumes as the fight was in start.\nHEROIC CHANGES: Boss also knocks back and can knock off platform. Tank can avoid by holding her in middle until last phase, when you must be careful due to Burning Breath from adds. Adds also knock back when they come out, so be careful!"

--Legion By Horrorbrood
--Dungeons
--Eye of Azshara
L["encounter:91784"] = "Tank:\n Taunt Adds that Spawn, stay out of the way of Impaling Spear\nDPS:\n kill adds and inturrup... as they spawn killing Hatecoil Crushers frist. Adds can be killed by directing Impaling Spear at an add\nHealer:\nHeal players with Throw Spear Debuff and Impaling Spear Targets, avoid Crashing Wave\nHeroic/Mythic:\n Boss Summons two adds and Crushing Wave will leave Pools Of Quicksand that slow and deal damange"
L["encounter:91789"] = "When Lady Hate Coil Casts Static Nova stand on a sand pile, when she casts Focused Lightning stand on water. Kill adds as they spawn tank must pick them up.\nHeroic/Mythic:\nMonsoon small tornado that targets players and destroys sand dunes, kite monsoon away from dunes close to party"
L["encounter:91808"] = "KILL ALL ADDS AROUND BOSS\n Move from poison on ground, at 66% health Serpentrix will Submerge and respawn with 2 Blazing Hydra Dps must kill and inturrupt their AOE spell while tank stays in melee range of Serpentrix and intruppts AOE spell. Repeat at 33%\n If hydras are not killed they will remain during the entire fight\nHeroic/Mythic:\nNew hyra in place of one blazing hydra. Arcane hydra cat Arcane Nova must be inturruped to avoid stacking debuff First priority "
L["encounter:91797"] = "Tank:\nMove out of the  Ground Slam Move away from the  Aftershock area after Deepbeard casts  Quake Save powerful cooldowns for the final 30%, when Deepbeard enters a  Frenzy King Deepbeard\nDPS:\nSpread out greater than 5 yards from one another in preparation for  Quake .Move out of the  Aftershock area after Deepbeard casts Quake.If affected by  Gaseous Bubbles, do not chase the  Call the Seas puddles around - wait for  Quake, and stand in the  Aftershock area to clear the bubble Stay away from the front of the boss to avoid being affected by Ground Slam\nHealer:\nSame as Dps but tank requires more healing during Frenzy.\nHeroic/Mythic:\nthe damage dealt by  Gaseous Explosion is proportional to the amount of damage absorption left on the  Gaseous Bubbles when it expires"
L["encounter:96028"] = "Dodge Massive Deluge, Tank keep the Wrath of Azshara facing about 90 degrees away from the party so no other players are threatened by it.Do not step into the pool in the center of the island.Avoid the Tidal Waves and  Mystic Tornado spawns near you.Step out of any  Lightning Strike areas near you. Tank Use stronger cooldowns during the Cry of Wrath phase.If targeted with  Arcane Bomb, move out to the edge of the island, wait for the debuff to be dispelled, then move away from the  Arcane Bomb\nHeroic/Mythic:Crushing Depths targets a non-tank player. Dps should stand in this to divide damage delt."
--Halls of Valor
